"signal_description": "The SIGNAL query is selecting three columns: 'Avg. Cycle Time', 'Avg. Inv. Payment Time', and 'PO Plant' from a subquery. In the subquery, it calculates the average cycle time by subtracting the first end time from the last end time. It also calculates the average invoice payment time by subtracting the first end time where the event name is either 'Record Invoice Receipt' or 'Create FI Invoice' from the last end time where the event name is 'Clear Invoice'. It also sums up the 'Last FI Invoice Item Gross Amount Local Curr.' column and renames it as 'Invoice Amount (INR)'. It also renames the 'PO Item Plant Name' column as 'PO Plant'. All these operations are performed on the 'defaultview-124' table. The results are then ordered by the third column in descending order."
